Chart patterns that breakout of a clear horizontal boundary are generally more reliable than patterns breaking out of a diagonal boundary
Chart patterns with a minimum of large spindles are generally more reliable than patterns with large spindles

In terms of reliability, smaller time frame patterns are more likely to fail/morph than patterns of each successive larger time frame.
Larger patterns (weeklies) are comprised of numerous lower time frame patterns (daily, intra-day) that failed or morphed
@TimmyBLee The pattern is useful for increasing sizing of a trade only when the pattern becomes the ignition to launch a larger chart construction, which for c___t__s is not the case

Comment on overbought/oversold indicators (RSI, Stochastic, et al)
Bull markets become & stay overbought
Huge bull markets become & stay hugely overbought
Oversold markets are much more prone to mean-reversion than are overbought markets
